GURGOYLE

Gurgoyles are the elite variant of Gargoyles: larger, stronger, and even
more fearsome.  Where Gargoyles serve as the infantry of the Gargoyle Empire,
Gurgoyles are commanders and champions.  Their MDC values and Supernatural
attributes significantly exceed those of common Gargoyles.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 6-16   ME: 5-20   MA: 4-14   PS: 20-45 (Supernatural)
  PP: 7-22   PE: 15-40  PB: 2-7    Spd: 11-26

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 4d6 x10 (approx 40-240 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons (higher MDC than Gargoyle)
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance (exceptional values)
  - Natural flight (wings)
  - Nightvision 300 ft
  - Claws and teeth as MDC weapons

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Horrific appearance; universally feared
  - Kill-on-sight policy from most humanoid factions

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

